It was a little hard to take.

50:31.129 --> 50:32.962
I see.

50:35.432 --> 50:37.166
I want to go home.

50:37.168 --> 50:38.834
Not yet.

50:38.836 --> 50:42.805
I want to go.
I'm feeling really bad.

50:42.807 --> 50:44.373
Yeah.

50:44.375 --> 50:46.642
- Very, very sad.
- Well, it's okay to feel sad.

50:46.644 --> 50:50.312
Thank you for your permission!
I don't like you.

50:50.314 --> 50:52.348
Why? 'Cause I told you
the truth?

50:52.350 --> 50:55.618
I don't know. I don't know
how to think about this.

50:55.620 --> 50:58.554
Are you just being mean to me?

50:58.556 --> 51:02.091
No. No, not at all.

51:02.093 --> 51:04.660
Well, it feels like it.

51:04.662 --> 51:07.463
I told you I like you.

51:07.465 --> 51:09.165
Really?

51:09.167 --> 51:10.566
Yeah.

51:10.568 --> 51:12.501
You're one of the few.

51:12.503 --> 51:16.205
The few that's strong enough to
see the world as it really is.

51:16.207 --> 51:20.876
Not the way the stories say
it is or pretend it should be.

51:20.878 --> 51:23.746
But the truth...

51:23.748 --> 51:25.748
is very simple

51:25.750 --> 51:28.217
and very ugly.

51:28.219 --> 51:30.786
And you're strong enough
to see that and face it

51:30.788 --> 51:33.255
and move on.

51:33.257 --> 51:35.391
- No, I'm not.
- You are.

51:35.393 --> 51:37.760
No, don't cry, don't cry.

51:37.762 --> 51:39.795
Come here, come here.

51:39.797 --> 51:43.866
[crying]

51:43.868 --> 51:45.935
It's okay.

51:50.407 --> 51:53.909
Oh, you're delicate.
So, so delicate.

51:53.911 --> 51:55.377
Oh.

51:55.379 --> 51:57.947
Thank you.

51:58.882 --> 52:00.883
I needed to cry.

52:00.885 --> 52:02.318
Right.

52:05.789 --> 52:07.356
It's okay.

52:29.446 --> 52:33.415
Well, this has been
quite an evening.

52:33.417 --> 52:34.917
Yeah.

52:34.919 --> 52:37.586
That kiss.

52:37.588 --> 52:39.021
Yes.

52:39.023 --> 52:41.090
What did it mean?

52:41.092 --> 52:42.725
You know.

52:47.697 --> 52:49.698
I want to go home.

52:49.700 --> 52:51.300
Where is your home?

52:51.302 --> 52:54.870
Your uncle's apartment?

52:54.872 --> 52:59.074
I think you are
very beautiful.

52:59.076 --> 53:00.543
Exquisite.

53:02.479 --> 53:04.146
Really.

53:04.148 --> 53:07.016
I thought you liked
blondes with big boobs.

53:07.018 --> 53:08.350
Them too.

53:08.352 --> 53:11.453
This is all getting
a little crazy.

53:11.455 --> 53:13.622
I know.

53:13.624 --> 53:14.723
I'm scared.

53:14.725 --> 53:16.325
It's just feeling alive, Manya.

53:16.327 --> 53:18.928
No, no, it's not.
It's fear.

53:18.930 --> 53:21.530
I want to sleep with you.

53:21.532 --> 53:23.632
No.

53:23.634 --> 53:25.768
No.

53:25.770 --> 53:28.237
Yes, yes.

53:28.239 --> 53:29.738
I don't want to.

53:29.740 --> 53:32.808
Well, you don't have any choice.

53:32.810 --> 53:34.843
Of course I do.

53:34.845 --> 53:39.014
No, not tonight. I told you,
I always get what I want.

53:41.184 --> 53:44.520
You don't want to do that.

53:44.522 --> 53:46.855
Yes, I do.

53:50.327 --> 53:53.629
You're a nice person.

53:53.631 --> 53:56.198
No, I'm not.

54:01.204 --> 54:03.706
Help! Help!

54:04.774 --> 54:08.677
[doorknob rattles]

54:08.679 --> 54:16.085
[random touch tones]

54:16.087 --> 54:17.853
Help!

54:17.855 --> 54:21.357
[touch tones continue]

54:21.359 --> 54:24.360
Help!

54:36.973 --> 54:38.474
No.

54:38.476 --> 54:40.476
- [cloth tears]
- [scream]

54:42.112 --> 54:43.746
Please!

54:46.883 --> 54:49.518
[sobbing]

55:06.536 --> 55:08.270
I know.
It looks ridiculous,

55:08.272 --> 55:10.773
but I've saved
a lot of shirts this way.

55:20.283 --> 55:22.518
I feel like we're in church.

55:22.520 --> 55:23.619
You are.

55:23.621 --> 55:26.755
No, I mean with
the candles and the mood.

55:26.757 --> 55:29.391
Well, a meal is
a sacrament, right?

55:29.393 --> 55:31.160
I don't know about that, but...

55:31.162 --> 55:34.296
it looks and smells
absolutely sensational.

55:36.366 --> 55:37.700
We thank thee, Lord,

55:37.702 --> 55:39.635
for this food
we're about to receive,

55:39.637 --> 55:42.104
for the company
about to receive it.

55:42.106 --> 55:45.074
May you bathe us all
in your mercy.

55:45.076 --> 55:46.375
We need it.

55:48.244 --> 55:50.713
- Amen.
- Amen.

55:50.715 --> 55:52.614
Bon appétit.

55:57.821 --> 55:59.254
Mmm.

56:01.257 --> 56:04.526
This is exquisite. You said
it's stuffed with four cheeses?

56:04.528 --> 56:07.896
Ricotta, mozzarella,
gorgonzola dolce and Reggiano.

56:07.898 --> 56:10.432
The flavor's so rich,
it's just...

56:10.434 --> 56:11.834
I'm glad you like it.

56:11.836 --> 56:13.335
I was afraid you'd
lose your appetites,

56:13.337 --> 56:15.170
and all my work
would be for naught.

56:15.172 --> 56:17.139
The one thing is
I can always eat.

56:17.141 --> 56:19.274
When I'm happy,
I eat to celebrate.

56:19.276 --> 56:21.744
And if I'm unhappy,
I eat to feel better.

56:21.746 --> 56:24.646
Oh! I forgot the wine!

56:24.648 --> 56:29.218
It's not a proper meal
without wine, is it?

56:31.187 --> 56:33.322
Uncle, will you do the honors?

56:36.526 --> 56:39.027
Thanks.

56:39.029 --> 56:42.364
You know, Alan, there were
some things you said last year

56:42.366 --> 56:44.600
I've thought a lot about.

56:44.602 --> 56:45.501
What things?

56:45.503 --> 56:47.970
About not running away,

56:47.972 --> 56:49.671
confronting things head-on.

56:49.673 --> 56:52.574
Like your parents' death?

56:52.576 --> 56:54.309
Or what happened last year?

56:54.311 --> 56:57.880
Yes. Bad things.

56:59.249 --> 57:02.618
May we always remember
this evening.

57:02.620 --> 57:04.186
Amen.

57:04.188 --> 57:05.788
Hear, hear.

57:11.494 --> 57:13.228
Other things, too.

57:13.230 --> 57:15.664
You talked about
using your power.

57:15.666 --> 57:16.732
Yes.

57:16.734 --> 57:19.368
About how young I was,
how innocent.

57:19.370 --> 57:20.869
You were.

57:20.871 --> 57:22.471
What I really
think about, though,

57:22.473 --> 57:25.707
is the price you pay
when you lose it.

57:25.709 --> 57:31.747
You see, it's important to me
to be a good person.

57:31.749 --> 57:36.018
When I was innocent,
that really wasn't a problem.

57:36.020 --> 57:41.223
But now, well, I realize
I'm really capable of anything.

57:41.225 --> 57:42.424
Anything?

57:42.426 --> 57:46.428
And that scares me.
It really does.

57:46.430 --> 57:48.464
I don't know what you're
talking about, kid.

57:48.466 --> 57:50.599
You still seem like
a sweetheart to me.

57:50.601 --> 57:53.702
Then maybe I should tell you
the rest of my story.

57:53.704 --> 57:56.138
So now the truth comes out,
does it?

57:56.140 --> 57:59.975
When I got back to college,
everything was very strange,

57:59.977 --> 58:03.111
like I was looking at the world
from a great distance,

58:03.113 --> 58:06.949
just observing, watching what
other people did, what I did,

58:06.951 --> 58:10.586
like it was all happening
on television.

58:10.588 --> 58:14.957
And I'd laugh at people
or cry at inappropriate times,

58:14.959 --> 58:18.160
like the other students
weren't really there.

58:18.162 --> 58:21.430
They were just this show
I was watching.

58:21.432 --> 58:23.298
My friends tolerated it
at first,

58:23.300 --> 58:26.935
but after about a week or so,
they started to avoid me,

58:26.937 --> 58:30.172
except for my friend Sarah,
who was pre-med also

58:30.174 --> 58:32.674
and who I always studied with.

58:32.676 --> 58:34.776
Sarah teased me,
called me "Zombie."

58:34.778 --> 58:37.613
She'd tell me, "Come eat now,"
and I'd go eat,

58:37.615 --> 58:41.049
or if it was time
to go to class.

58:41.051 --> 58:43.285
She was kind of my nurse.

58:43.287 --> 58:45.087
Around Christmastime,

58:45.089 --> 58:50.292
in that distant way
I was observing everything,

58:50.294 --> 58:52.294
I realized I was pregnant.

58:52.296 --> 58:53.829
What?

58:53.831 --> 58:56.765
I said to myself,
"Manya missed her period.

58:56.767 --> 58:58.967
- She might be pregnant."
- From me, Manya?

58:58.969 --> 59:00.269
And I liked it.

59:00.271 --> 59:02.204
It's like it made the show
more interesting.

59:02.206 --> 59:06.708
Wait, wait, wait.
Are you saying I'm the father?

59:06.710 --> 59:09.845
There wasn't
anyone else, Alan.

59:09.847 --> 59:13.048
You got pregnant
from one fuck?

59:13.050 --> 59:14.550
One fuck, one sperm.

59:14.552 --> 59:17.085
That's kind of
all it takes, right?

59:17.087 --> 59:18.453
How it happens?

59:18.455 --> 59:20.055
Right, but I...

59:20.057 --> 59:22.491
I ate compulsively,
and I gained a lot of weight.

59:22.493 --> 59:24.359
25 pounds
by the end of January.

59:24.361 --> 59:27.129
Hold on.
I think I figured it out,

59:27.131 --> 59:29.665
why you invited me here
tonight.

59:29.667 --> 59:30.666
Why?

59:30.668 --> 59:32.401
You want me to pay
for your baby.

59:32.403 --> 59:34.870
<i>Our</i> baby.

59:34.872 --> 59:39.541
And yes, Alan,
I want you to pay.

59:39.543 --> 59:41.577
Where's the baby?

59:44.147 --> 59:47.082
I kept watching myself.

59:47.084 --> 59:49.651
Watch Manya gain 30 pounds.

59:49.653 --> 59:52.521
Watch her freak everyone out
by not talking.

59:52.523 --> 59:54.656
Watch her study
for 12 hours a day

59:54.658 --> 59:57.025
and ace all of her tests.

59:57.027 --> 59:59.227
Finally, Sarah couldn't
take it anymore.

59:59.229 --> 01:00:00.729
She screamed, slapped me,

01:00:00.731 --> 01:00:03.131
told me I had to come back
from wherever I was

01:00:03.133 --> 01:00:06.602
or she'd abandon me
just like everyone else.

01:00:06.604 --> 01:00:08.070
Did you have the baby?

01:00:08.072 --> 01:00:09.871
- I didn't.
- What?

01:00:09.873 --> 01:00:12.908
The odd thing was it didn't
occur to me for a long time

01:00:12.910 --> 01:00:16.078
that being pregnant meant
that I was going to have a baby.

01:00:16.080 --> 01:00:18.113
Rape Baby, I called it.

01:00:18.115 --> 01:00:20.515
The baby started kicking.

01:00:20.517 --> 01:00:22.918
And that's what
brought me out of it.

01:00:22.920 --> 01:00:26.188
Plus my back hurt,
and I was getting hemorrhoids.

01:00:26.190 --> 01:00:32.361
And it finally hit me
that this wasn't TV.

01:00:32.363 --> 01:00:35.063
I was really in this fat body,

01:00:35.065 --> 01:00:39.635
and this fat body really did
have a baby inside of it.

01:00:39.637 --> 01:00:42.604
And I was really
gonna have that baby

01:00:42.606 --> 01:00:44.573
unless I did something
about it.

01:00:44.575 --> 01:00:46.174
So I went to a doctor
in Philly.

01:00:46.176 --> 01:00:47.843
An abortionist.

01:00:47.845 --> 01:00:50.646
Yeah, but he wouldn't do it
because I was so far along.

01:00:50.648 --> 01:00:51.947
I would think not.

01:00:51.949 --> 01:00:54.549
And even though
I'd been raped,

01:00:54.551 --> 01:00:56.151
well, after a certain point,

01:00:56.153 --> 01:00:59.621
it stops being an abortion,
technically speaking,

01:00:59.623 --> 01:01:02.491
and it becomes
a premature delivery.

01:01:02.493 --> 01:01:04.092
A murder.

01:01:05.328 --> 01:01:06.828
Yes.

01:01:08.598 --> 01:01:10.732
So no other doctor
would touch it either.

01:01:10.734 --> 01:01:15.237
And then one night,
a very black night alone,

01:01:15.239 --> 01:01:16.638
it came to me.

01:01:16.640 --> 01:01:18.740
I talked to Sarah,

01:01:18.742 --> 01:01:21.009
and, well, I didn't tell her
the whole plan.

01:01:21.011 --> 01:01:22.010
What plan?

01:01:22.012 --> 01:01:23.879
She was going out
with this guy

01:01:23.881 --> 01:01:26.815
who graduated the year before
and was in med school at Penn.

01:01:26.817 --> 01:01:28.583
A really sweet guy. Phillip.

01:01:28.585 --> 01:01:30.752
I mean, he was nuts
to do what he did,

01:01:30.754 --> 01:01:34.690
but he gave us what we needed
and told Sarah what to do,

01:01:34.692 --> 01:01:36.925
and we figured
we could pull it off.

01:01:36.927 --> 01:01:38.593
- Pull what off?
- Abort it.

01:01:38.595 --> 01:01:41.530
You aborted
a six-month-old baby?

01:01:41.532 --> 01:01:43.865
25 weeks.

01:01:45.668 --> 01:01:48.603
- Was it born alive?
- No.

01:01:48.605 --> 01:01:50.605
But it might have been, right?

01:01:50.607 --> 01:01:52.607
Not the way we did it.

01:01:52.609 --> 01:01:54.710
You killed the baby.

01:01:56.279 --> 01:01:57.879
My baby.

01:01:57.881 --> 01:02:00.582
Yes. You fathered a child,

01:02:00.584 --> 01:02:03.719
and I let it grow
until it was pretty big

01:02:03.721 --> 01:02:05.520
and its heart was beating.

01:02:05.522 --> 01:02:09.691
But I didn't want it to live,
and so I killed it.

01:02:09.693 --> 01:02:13.795
I did to it
what you did to me.

01:02:15.565 --> 01:02:17.265
No.

01:02:17.267 --> 01:02:18.567
Not at all.

01:02:18.569 --> 01:02:22.604
It felt pretty close.

01:02:22.606 --> 01:02:26.408
Was it a boy or a girl?

01:02:26.410 --> 01:02:29.077
This is how we did it.

01:02:29.079 --> 01:02:32.614
Phillip gave us
an empty syringe, a speculum,

01:02:32.616 --> 01:02:34.416
another syringe
full of saline.

01:02:34.418 --> 01:02:37.886
Oh, and then in case
things didn't go smoothly,

01:02:37.888 --> 01:02:41.323
this thing about that long,

01:02:41.325 --> 01:02:43.825
called an "amniotic hook."

01:02:43.827 --> 01:02:46.027
The medical equivalent
of a knitting needle.

01:02:46.029 --> 01:02:48.396
- I don't believe this.
- I know!

01:02:48.398 --> 01:02:51.767
And it was the worst time
of year, final exams.

01:02:51.769 --> 01:02:54.603
But I had a week between
my bio and chem finals

01:02:54.605 --> 01:02:56.104
and another week before orals,

01:02:56.106 --> 01:02:58.774
so we figured
I'd make it through.

01:02:58.776 --> 01:03:02.210
Phillip made it clear to Sarah
and indirectly to me

01:03:02.212 --> 01:03:05.113
that what we were doing
was very dangerous.

01:03:05.115 --> 01:03:07.249
And completely illegal.

01:03:08.651 --> 01:03:10.485
Oh, sorry, Alan.

01:03:10.487 --> 01:03:13.789
Legal, illegal. I didn't think
those things concerned you.

01:03:15.558 --> 01:03:18.894
As I was saying, dangerous.

01:03:18.896 --> 01:03:20.862
If the fetus doesn't
come out quickly,

01:03:20.864 --> 01:03:24.166
severe, even fatal infection
is pretty likely.

01:03:24.168 --> 01:03:25.867
I didn't care.

01:03:25.869 --> 01:03:28.737
I knew exactly
what I wanted to do.

01:03:28.739 --> 01:03:32.707
First, I peed,
emptied the bladder.

01:03:32.709 --> 01:03:34.810
Then Sarah gave me
a local anesthetic

01:03:34.812 --> 01:03:36.711
and prepared the needle.

01:03:36.713 --> 01:03:37.946
I hate needles,

01:03:37.948 --> 01:03:40.348
and this mother
had a 14-gauge bore.

01:03:40.350 --> 01:03:42.751
It was huge.

01:03:44.387 --> 01:03:46.188
She felt around for my uterus

01:03:46.190 --> 01:03:48.757
and stuck the needle
straight through my belly.

01:03:48.759 --> 01:03:50.959
- Jesus.
- First she pulls the plunger

01:03:50.961 --> 01:03:53.829
and takes out 100 CCs
of amniotic fluid,

01:03:53.831 --> 01:03:56.665
then she switches the syringe
and injects 50 CCs

01:03:56.667 --> 01:04:00.902
of hypertonic super-saturated
saline solution.

01:04:00.904 --> 01:04:04.039
That's what killed the baby.

01:04:04.041 --> 01:04:06.074
Yes.

01:04:06.076 --> 01:04:08.577
- Sounds efficient.
- Yep.

01:04:08.579 --> 01:04:12.147
Can you speed this up?
It's a little hard to take.

01:04:12.149 --> 01:04:13.381
Right?

01:04:13.383 --> 01:04:14.983
So then we wait.

01:04:14.985 --> 01:04:17.686
Nothing happens.
No contractions.

01:04:17.688 --> 01:04:19.688
The saline,
as well as killing the kid,

01:04:19.690 --> 01:04:21.122
is supposed to induce labor,

01:04:21.124 --> 01:04:23.592
but my uterus
hadn't read the textbooks.

01:04:23.594 --> 01:04:27.963
I just lay there in
this kind of existential hell.

01:04:27.965 --> 01:04:31.766
Sarah's sipping Diet Coke
and studying for her exams,

01:04:31.768 --> 01:04:35.370
and I'm just waiting.

01:04:36.806 --> 01:04:40.275
Through all this,
what keeps me going is my anger.

01:04:40.277 --> 01:04:44.713
A light, an ugliness
shining in the distance.

01:04:44.715 --> 01:04:48.316
Very far away,
but clear and bright.

01:04:48.318 --> 01:04:50.518
And every time
I start to freak out,

01:04:50.520 --> 01:04:53.188
I close my eyes and see it.

01:04:53.190 --> 01:04:55.657
You know that anger,
don't you, Alan?

01:04:55.659 --> 01:04:57.959
Everyone knows it, my dear,

01:04:57.961 --> 01:05:00.962
but only a few of us
are able to harness it.

01:05:00.964 --> 01:05:02.697
Yes.

01:05:02.699 --> 01:05:06.968
Phillip told us if the fetus
didn't come out in 12 hours,

01:05:06.970 --> 01:05:08.536
we should use the hook.

01:05:08.538 --> 01:05:11.506
But the hook increases
the risk of infection.

01:05:11.508 --> 01:05:13.508
Sarah didn't want to try it.

01:05:13.510 --> 01:05:14.743
I forced her.

01:05:14.745 --> 01:05:17.112
My cervix is
slightly dilated now,

01:05:17.114 --> 01:05:19.614
and so she reaches up there
with this thing.

01:05:19.616 --> 01:05:21.416
Poke and pull,
poke and pull.

01:05:21.418 --> 01:05:24.219
The damn bag is slippery.
And Sarah's crying

01:05:24.221 --> 01:05:26.688
because she's afraid
she's gonna tear me open.

01:05:26.690 --> 01:05:28.023
But she doesn't.

01:05:28.025 --> 01:05:31.526
- The water finally bursts.
- Thank God.

01:05:31.528 --> 01:05:34.062
Philip says if the baby
doesn't come right out,

01:05:34.064 --> 01:05:36.264
we have to go to the hospital.

01:05:36.266 --> 01:05:38.833
Sarah's in a panic.
What if I die?

01:05:38.835 --> 01:05:40.835
What if she's arrested
for manslaughter?

01:05:40.837 --> 01:05:42.704
But I refuse to go.

01:05:42.706 --> 01:05:46.741
No doctors, no hospitals,
no nurses.

01:05:46.743 --> 01:05:49.144
It has to be
just me and Sarah.

01:05:49.146 --> 01:05:52.247
"It's going to be okay,"
I tell her.

01:05:52.249 --> 01:05:55.784
Everything's going to be okay.

01:05:57.620 --> 01:06:02.857
By midnight, 15 hours,

01:06:02.859 --> 01:06:07.228
Rape Baby finally comes out.

01:06:07.230 --> 01:06:09.097
Jesus Christ.

01:06:09.099 --> 01:06:11.099
She cleaned up,
and every hour or so,

01:06:11.101 --> 01:06:13.501
she'd come back
to check on the bleeding.

01:06:13.503 --> 01:06:15.971
- You hemorrhaged?
- Some.

01:06:15.973 --> 01:06:18.740
